      <hedline>
        <hl1>Joy in Gotham: New York Takes Series!</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bernard Scharfstein letter comments on October 18 article on New York Yankees defeat of Seattle Mariners to capture 37th American League pennant</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Yanks Win 37th Pennant With a Comeback Effort'' (front page, Oct. 18):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Yanks Win 37th Pennant With a Comeback Effort'' (front page, Oct. 18):</p>
        <p>It would be appropriate in our Subway Series to have a victory celebration that would include the winner and the loser. It is, after all, a celebration for all New Yorkers.</p>
        <p>BERNARD SCHARFSTEIN  New York, Oct. 18, 2000</p>
      </block>
